Definition: far-reaching and thoroughgoing in effect especially on the nature of something
Example: the fundamental revolution in human values that has occurred; the book underwent fundamental changes; committed the fundamental error of confusing spending with extravagance; profound social changes
Synonyms: profound, noun, cognition, profoundness, far-reaching, and, thoroughgoing, in, effect, especially, on, the, nature, of, something, revolution, human, values, that, has, occurred, book, underwent, changes, committed, error, confusing, spending, with, extravagance, social
Category: adj.all
